---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---
<BaseLayout title="BridgeAIChat Beta" description="Run one chat interface for AI CLIs across your own devices.">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="surface">
      <div class="eyebrow">Developer Control Plane</div>
      <h1>Operate the AI tools on your machines from one chat surface.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        BridgeAIChat gives you a shared UI for Codex, Claude, and other CLI-native tools running on your laptop,
        desktop, VPS, or Raspberry Pi. The gateway stays on your side, the agents stay on your devices, and Tailscale
        ties discovery and private routing together.
      </p>
      <div class="pill-row">
        <span class="pill">Tailnet login beta</span>
        <span class="pill">GitHub release install</span>
        <span class="pill">Self-hosted control plane</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a class="button primary" href="/downloads">Install the beta</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href="/docs/quickstart">Read the quickstart</a>
      </div>
      <div class="metric-grid">
        <div class="metric">
          <strong>1 UI</strong>
          <span>for your laptop, VPS, and edge boxes</span>
        </div>
        <div class="metric">
          <strong>0 hosted runtime</strong>
          <span>required for the current beta</span>
        </div>
        <div class="metric">
          <strong>3 states</strong>
          <span>Connected, Agent Missing, and Offline</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="terminal">
      <div class="terminal-bar">
        <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
        <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
        <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
      </div>
      <pre>export TAILSCALE_CLIENT_ID=tsid_xxx
export TAILSCALE_CLIENT_SECRET=tssecret_xxx
export TAILSCALE_API_BASE=https://api.tailscale.com/api/v2
export APP_URL=http://localhost:8080

bridge-gateway

# then in the browser
Continue with Tailscale
tail427f1a.ts.net

# on another device
bash install-agent.sh</pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gap grid three">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="eyebrow">Own the Runtime</div>
      <h2>Keep execution where your tools already live.</h2>
      <p>BridgeAIChat does not replace your local CLI tools. It wraps them with a better control surface and a device-aware transport layer.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="eyebrow">Fleet Visibility</div>
      <h2>See which machine is reachable.</h2>
      <p>The UI merges Tailscale device status with live Bridge agents so you can immediately tell whether a machine is connected, missing an agent, or offline.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="eyebrow">Beta Shape</div>
      <h2>Simple login, simple networking.</h2>
      <p>The beta uses a tailnet input form instead of Tailscale user auth. The gateway handles device discovery with your Tailscale API credentials.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gap grid two">
    <div class="card stack">
      <div class="eyebrow">How It Works</div>
      <h2>Minimal architecture, clear boundaries.</h2>
      <div class="note"><strong>bridge-ai-app</strong> runs the gateway and serves the UI.</div>
      <div class="note"><strong>bridge-ai-agent</strong> runs on each remote machine and bridges to local AI CLIs.</div>
      <div class="note"><strong>bridge-ai-docs</strong> is the install guide and beta reference site.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="card stack">
      <div class="eyebrow">Best Fit</div>
      <h2>Who the beta is for.</h2>
      <ul class="list tight">
        <li>Developers using Codex or Claude CLI on more than one machine</li>
        <li>Homelab operators with GPU boxes, VPS hosts, or Raspberry Pi nodes</li>
        <li>Platform engineers who want a private, inspectable AI runtime path</li>
        <li>Early testers comfortable running the gateway with local Tailscale credentials</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
